TITLE: Creating a Floating Image in docx
DESCRIPTION: Creates a floating image that appears on top of text with specified positioning. This snippet demonstrates setting the image type, data source, dimensions, and floating position with offsets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/images.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const image = new ImageRun({
    type: 'gif',
    data: fs.readFileSync("./demo/images/pizza.gif"),
    transformation: {
        width: 200,
        height: 200,
    }
    floating: {
        horizontalPosition: {
            offset: 1014400,
        },
        verticalPosition: {
            offset: 1014400,
        },
    },
});
```

