TITLE: Declarative Styles Definition
DESCRIPTION: Example of defining custom paragraph styles in a document including custom formatting for runs and paragraphs. Demonstrates style inheritance and complex formatting options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/styling-with-js.md#2025-04-20_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const doc = new Document({
    creator: "Clippy",
    title: "Sample Document",
    description: "A brief example of using docx",
    styles: {
        paragraphStyles: [
            {
                id: "myWonkyStyle",
                name: "My Wonky Style",
                basedOn: "Normal",
                next: "Normal",
                quickFormat: true,
                run: {
                    italics: true,
                    color: "999999",
                },
                paragraph: {
                    spacing: {
                        line: 276,
                    },
                    indent: {
                        left: 720,
                    },
                },
            },
            {
                id: "Heading2",
                name: "Heading 2",
                basedOn: "Normal",
                next: "Normal",
                quickFormat: true,
                run: {
                    size: 26,
                    bold: true,
                    color: "999999",
                    underline: {
                        type: UnderlineType.DOUBLE,
                        color: "FF0000",
                    },
                },
                paragraph: {
                    spacing: {
                        before: 240,
                        after: 120
                    },
                },
            },
        ]
    }
});
```

