TITLE: Loading External Styles from XML File in docx
DESCRIPTION: Creates a Document object with external styles loaded from a styles.xml file extracted from a Word document. This allows the document to use custom styles defined in Microsoft Word.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/styling-with-xml.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const styles = fs.readFileSync("./styles.xml", "utf-8");
const doc = new docx.Document({
    title: "Title",
    externalStyles: styles,
});
```

