TITLE: Creating External Hyperlinks in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create an external hyperlink that points to a URL outside the document. It includes styled text and the target URL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/hyperlinks.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const paragraph = new Paragraph({
    children: [
        new ExternalHyperlink({
            children: [
                new TextRun({
                    text: "This is an external link!",
                    style: "Hyperlink",
                }),
            ],
            link: "https://docx.js.org",
        }),
    ],
});
```

