TITLE: Configuring Document Numbering with Custom Formatting in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a custom numbering configuration in a Document instance. It demonstrates setting up a numbering style with Roman numerals, custom alignment, and paragraph indentation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/numbering.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const doc = new Document({
    ...
    numbering: {
        config: [
            {
                reference: "my-numbering",
                levels: [
                    {
                        level: 0,
                        format: LevelFormat.UPPER_ROMAN,
                        text: "%1",
                        alignment: AlignmentType.START,
                        style: {
                            paragraph: {
                                indent: { left: 2880, hanging: 2420 },
                            },
                        },
                    },
                    ...
                ],
            },
        ],
    },
    ...
});
```

