TITLE: Basic Text and Paragraph Formatting in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Examples of basic text and paragraph formatting using direct formatting approach. Shows how to create paragraphs with heading styles and alignment, and text runs with bold, font and caps formatting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/styling-with-js.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const para = new Paragraph({
    text: "To whom it may concern:",
    heading: HeadingLevel.HEADING_2,
    alignment: AlignmentType.CENTER,
});

const name = new TextRun({
    text: "Name:",
    bold: true,
    font: "Calibri",
    allCaps: true,
});
```

