TITLE: Implementing Comments in DOCX Documents with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to add comments to a document using the docx library. It shows how to define comment authors, create the comments block, and place comments in the document using both comment ranges and comment references.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/comments.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import * as fs from "fs";
import {
    CommentRangeEnd,
    CommentRangeStart,
    CommentReference,
    Document,
    Packer,
    Paragraph,
    TextRun,
} from "docx";

const doc = new Document({
    comments: {
        // Defines the comments for the document
        comments: [
            {
                id: 0,
                text: "Is this right?",
                author: "John Doe",
                date: new Date(2020, 3, 20),
            },
            {
                id: 1,
                text: "Yes, it is!",
                author: "Jane Doe",
                date: new Date(2020, 3, 21),
            },
        ],
    },
    sections: [
        {
            properties: {},
            children: [
                new Paragraph({
                    children: [
                        new TextRun("Hello World"),
                        new CommentRangeStart(0),
                        new TextRun(" with a comment"),
                        new CommentRangeEnd(0),
                        new CommentReference(0),
                    ],
                }),
                new Paragraph({
                    children: [
                        new TextRun("Hello again"),
                        new CommentReference(1),
                    ],
                }),
                new Paragraph({
                    children: [new TextRun("Some more text")],
                }),
            ],
        },
    ],
});

Packer.toBuffer(doc).then((buffer) => {
    fs.writeFileSync("My Document.docx", buffer);
});
```

