TITLE: Configuring Document with Paragraph Style for Bullet Points in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Creates a document with both numbering configuration and a paragraph style that uses this numbering. This allows bullet points to be applied through styles rather than directly on paragraphs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dolanmiu/docx/blob/master/docs/usage/numbering.md#2025-04-20_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const doc = new Document({
    ...
    numbering: {
        config: [
            {
                reference: "my-bullet-points",
                levels: [
                    {
                        level: 0,
                        format: LevelFormat.BULLET,
                        text: "\u1F60",
                        alignment: AlignmentType.LEFT,
                        style: {
                            paragraph: {
                                indent: { left: convertInchesToTwip(0.5), hanging: convertInchesToTwip(0.25) },
                            },
                        },
                    },
                ],
            },
        ],
    },
    styles: {
        paragraphStyles: [
            {
                id: 'bullet',
                name: 'Bullet',
                basedOn: 'Normal',
                next: 'Normal',
                run: {},
                paragraph: {
                    numbering: {
                        reference: 'my-bullet-points',
                        level: 0,
                    },
                },
            },
        ],
    },
    ...
});
```

